-- RWE Reorganizes German Operations as Rising Costs, Stagnant Prices Weigh
-- B y   A n g e l a   C u l l e n
-- 2010-09-23T11:57:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/rwe-reorganizes-german-operations-as-rising-costs-stagnant-prices-weigh.html
RWE AG plans to pool its German
operations from Jan. 1 and reduce its management board to five
as it seeks to counter the effects of climate protection
targets, rising raw material prices and a nuclear tax in
Germany, it said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
